        <!-- Slide 9: Why Nest.js & PostgreSQL? -->
        <div class="slide bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12 min-h-[70vh] md:min-h-[80vh]">
            <div class="slide-header flex justify-between items-center">
                <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-800">Why Nest.js & PostgreSQL?</h2>
                <span class="presenter-tag">Mir Muhitul</span>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mt-8">
                <div class="bg-red-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-3">Nest.js (Backend)</h3>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 text-slate-700">
                        <li><strong>Organized & Easy to Grow:</strong> Its neat structure makes it easy to manage and add new features later.</li>
                        <li><strong>Fast & Efficient:</strong> It can handle many users at once, which is perfect for a busy rental site.</li>
                        <li><strong>Uses JavaScript:</strong> This makes building the site faster and cheaper.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-700 mb-3">PostgreSQL (Database)</h3>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 text-slate-700">
                        <li><strong>Reliable for Bookings:</strong> Makes sure bookings and payments are handled correctly without any errors.</li>
                        <li><strong>Powerful Search:</strong> Lets users search for homes using many options (like price or location) very quickly.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

